svg.text: Each Instance gets the following installed at initial start (via user data):- the latest version of Cribl LogStream (current release)- the check-files.sh script (into /opt/cribl/scripts)
Notification is sent to the Lifecycle Hook

Lambda function uses SSM to access the instance, running /opt/cribl/scripts/check-files.sh on the instance targeted for termination.If the script exits gracefully, the lambda signals the ASG hook that it’s ok to proceed with termination. Otherwise, it doesn’t send any message to the ASG hook, leading the termination to wait until the heartbeat timeout has expired (giving you time to fix the destination to let it drain).
